What about n=-32768, d=65534? Not relevant since delta_en uses d=128, clamped sum uses d=2, amp_factor uses d=65534, prod01/new_am use d=65535.
4. **Overflow in int32(w1.ph) - int32(w2.ph)**: Since both are 0..65535, difference fits in int32 easily. No overflow.
